cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.CC, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with first-order logic and a Feferman-Vaught-type composition theorem for MSO.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses maintaining queries and updating stored results in response to changes in data.
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper deals with querying and updating data.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses AC$^1$-computable initialisation.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses decision and optimisation problems.
